er been to the planes, I've never seen an indoor dragon (Vox/Nag/Trak) and don't care if I ever do.  I play the game to have fun.  To level my toons, get neat new spells and to accomplish things that are within my ability.<br><br>I left Brell because I was sick of all the constant whining and in-fighting and backstabbing and cliques.  I don't recall ever taking part in any of it, but it sure was disheartening to see the same people whining and complaining about the same old stuff day in and day out.  Just because I never took part in raids here or there doesn't mean I didn't visit brellserilis.net everyday to keep on top of events.<br><br>My current server is NOTHING like some of you paint FCFS servers.  Dragons / Planes are not farmed.  Co-operation between guilds / groups of players is night and day compared to Brell.  If I wanted to go on a Hate raid tonight for example, there is a 99 percent chance I could attend one - if of course there was one planned by anyone.  If one wasn't planned, even a complete planer newbie like myself could raise a couple groups of experienced strangers to go by sending a few random tells.<br><br>I could go on, but it's very apparent that those who foretell doom and gloom by saying &quot;Check out a FCFS and you'll see how lucky we are&quot; have no clue as to how a FCFS server operates.<br><br>And yes, I still come back here to read the Brell forums once every couple of months or so.. partially to see if I recognize any names and to see the downfall of the lists. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=BEBEBE>Nillon the Champion</font><br><font color=red>Brell BoTB Winner</font></span><br>  Posts: 2391<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 3:57:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScr