ried many times to foster change in the system and hit a brick wall of nay-sayers and protectionists at every turn.  This is what started me down the path to FCFS advocacy.  But what really pushed me over the edge was Velious.  Kunark had helped....especially Gore/Talendor/Sev but the 2 biggest encounters were still reserved (VS/Trak).  Velious was like this big candy store where I could run around and no one was slapping my hand for pressing my nose against the display case.<br><br>I had seen enough......the VS list fiasco.....the attempt to make change to help the Asian and European guilds.....all shot to hell.  I had had enough.....it was time for a hard line stance against reservations.  People were just not being reasonable to help people that needed it......they just wanted to help themselves.<br><br>So that brings us to today.....another nail in the coffin of reserved MOB's and &quot;entitlement&quot; thinking I hope.....we'll see. <p><font size=2 face="Tempus Sans ITC, Verdana, Helvetica"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8687>Kulanae Soulsease</a></font><br><font size=2 face="Helvetica">Virtuoso of <a href=http://www.watchers-brell.com>Watchers</a><br><br><i>Joy is in the ears that hear!</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukestrithebard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KestriTheBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FF2222>Evil Board Mod</font></span><br>  Posts: 1411<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/21/02 8:06:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yeah</span><hr size=1> I can tell you everyone I have been a huge supporter of reservations when they are working.  When they no longer work I am also a full believer in change.  